## Vercel AI SDK Monorepo Structure - Comprehensive Analysis

I've thoroughly explored the Vercel AI SDK monorepo structure, focusing on the OpenAI and Google provider packages. Here's my detailed findings:

### 1. Overall Directory Structure

**packages/openai/** and **packages/google/** are two major AI provider packages that follow the same architectural pattern. The monorepo contains 55+ provider packages total.

### 2. File Structure of packages/openai/

**Root level files:**
- `package.json` - Package metadata and scripts
- `tsconfig.json` - TypeScript configuration
- `tsconfig.build.json` - Build-specific TypeScript config
- `tsup.config.ts` - Build configuration
- `vitest.node.config.js` and `vitest.edge.config.js` - Test configurations
- `turbo.json` - Turborepo configuration
- `README.md` and `CHANGELOG.md` - Documentation
- `internal.d.ts` - Internal type definitions

**Source directory (src/) organization:**
- `index.ts` - Main export file
- `openai-provider.ts` - Provider factory and main provider class
- `openai-config.ts` - Configuration handling
- `openai-error.ts` - Error handling
- `openai-tools.ts` - OpenAI-specific tools
- `openai-language-model-capabilities.ts` - Model capabilities
- `version.ts` - Version information
- `internal/index.ts` - Internal exports

**Feature subdirectories:**
- `chat/` - Chat completions API (6 files)
- `completion/` - Legacy completions API (5 files)
- `embedding/` - Text embeddings (4 files)
- `image/` - Image generation (4 files)
- `speech/` - Text-to-speech (4 files)
- `transcription/` - Speech-to-text (4 files)
- `responses/` - New responses API with advanced features (9 files)
- `tool/` - OpenAI tools (web-search, code-interpreter, file-search, custom, apply-patch, mcp, etc.)

Each feature directory typically contains:
- `<feature>-api.ts` - API communication
- `<feature>-language-model.ts` - Model implementation
- `<feature>-options.ts` - Configuration options
- Helper utilities (convert, map finish reasons, get metadata)
- Test files and fixtures

